### Sub-Link Scoped IPv6 Multicast Addressing
*Presented by David Lamparter*
* Draft: [draft-ietf-6man-sub-link-scope-multicast](../id/draft-ietf-6man-sub-link-scope-multicast.html)
* Slide Deck: [Sub-Link Scoped IPv6 Multicast Addressing](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/126/materials/slides-126-6man-sub-link-scoped-ipv6-multicast-addressing-00)

* **Discussion**:
  * The draft defines a mapping to use existing IEEE 802.1Q Layer 2 multicast groups that do not traverse bridges/switches. This enables LLDP-like discovery to stay strictly on the physical wire, which is highly useful in overlay networks like VXLAN.
  * It maps a reserved combination in the `ff22` prefix to the `01-80-c2` Ethernet multicast range.
  * David Lamparter noted that the implementation is incredibly simple (only 31 lines of code in the Linux kernel) and was successfully demoed at the Hackathon.
  * Bob Hinden suggested that the draft is in good shape and should proceed to a Working Group Last Call to gauge broader interest.

