### IPv6 Node Requirements
*Presented by Michael Ackermann*
* Draft: [draft-ietf-6man-rfc8504-bis](../id/draft-ietf-6man-rfc8504-bis.html)
* Slide Deck: [IPv6 Node Requirements](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/126/materials/slides-126-6man-ipv6-node-requirements-00)

* **Discussion**:
  * **Extension Headers**: The authors reverted the Extension Header limits text back to the original RFC 8504 text because the "limits" draft did not progress. 
  * Ron Bonica questioned whether the text allowing a host to "disallow unknown options" violates RFC 8200. Tim Chown and Michael Ackermann explained that this text has been in RFC 8504 since 2019 to protect end hosts, and the default behavior remains compliant with RFC 8200. Justin Iurman suggested using this text to align with [draft-ietf-6man-eh-occurrences](../id/draft-ietf-6man-eh-occurrences.html).
  * **PMTUD and DiffServ**: Explicit RFC references were added for PMTUD based on Gorry Fairhurst's feedback, and DiffServ was added alongside ECN.
  * **NAT64/PREF64 Discovery**: The draft proposed changing RFC 7050 to "may support" and RFC 8781 to "should support". 
    * Lorenzo Colitti requested removing the "should" for RFC 7050 entirely. 
    * Tim Chown and Jen Linkova discussed referencing RFC 9872 (which recommends RFC 8781 with an RFC 7050 fallback except on mobile networks) to avoid duplicate text.
    * Jordi Palet Martinez recommended deprecating RFC 7050 entirely, citing issues where it fails without RFC 8880.
    * Lorenzo Colitti suggested that the draft should require nodes to process the RA option (RFC 8781) and make the prefix available to user space, rather than specifying how the node performs local address synthesis.
  * **Address Selection & SLAAC Renum**: Lorenzo Colitti supported requiring the updated Default Address Selection (RFC 6724 bis). Tim Chown and Lorenzo Colitti agreed that [draft-ietf-6man-slaac-renum](../id/draft-ietf-6man-slaac-renum.html) should be integrated once it advances, though Lorenzo noted past disagreements on zero valid lifetime RAs.
  * **Next Steps**: The authors will publish version -04 incorporating feedback and request WGLC.

