### IPv6 Flow Label Load Balancing for RoCEv2
*Presented by Joanne*
* Slide Deck: [slides-126-6man-ipv6-flowlabel-load-balancing-rdma-01](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/126/materials/slides-126-6man-slides-126-6man-ipv6-flowlabel-load-balancing-rdma-01-00)

* **Discussion**:
  * The draft proposes using RoCEv2 Queue Pair (QP) numbers as entropy to generate the IPv6 Flow Label to prevent "elephant flows" from causing network congestion.
  * Ron Bonica and Jen Linkova pointed out that flow label generation is purely private host behavior (governed by RFC 6437/7098) and does not require standardization.
  * Jen Linkova noted that the abstract was confusing because it implied intermediate routers or switches would modify the flow label, whereas Joanne clarified that only the ingress node generating the packet does so.
  * Lorenzo Colitti questioned why the source ports could not simply be changed to achieve the same entropy.
  * **Action Item**: The authors will clarify the role of the ingress device in the next draft version.

